This RNAi clone targets to the transcript that was annotated as F02A9.4a in earlier WormBase versions, which corresponds to the WormBase ID WBGene00008514. This WormBase ID is linked to methylcrotonoyl-CoA carboxylase beta subunit in functional gene annotations such as WormCat or WormPath. However, transcript F02A9.4a was later reannotated to be an individual gene mccc-2, whose WBID is WBGene00303021 in WormBase. Meanwhile, WBGene00008514 gene was changed to mrpl-44. We confirmed that our RNAi clone targets to the ORF of newly defined mccc-2, which, however, has a short (~150bp) overlap with the ORF of mrpl-44. Therefore, the RNAi primarily targets to mccc-2 with a potential off-target effect on mrpl-44. We label the target gene information as mrpl-44/mccc-2 to indicate this historical issue as well as potential multiple targeting effects. For convenience, the gene name of this target gene is still used as mrpl-44 (WBGene00008514) in our rewiring analysis, to correctly link it to its functional annotations (methylcrotonoyl-CoA carboxylase beta subunit).
